  "prompt": "Is a passport compulsory to travel on flights within India?",
  "response": "No, a passport is **not** compulsory to travel on flights within India for Indian citizens.\n\nHowever, you **must** carry a valid photo ID. Acceptable forms of identification include:\n\n*   Aadhaar Card\n*   Voter ID\n*   PAN Card\n*   Driving License\n*   Government issued photo ID card\n*   Student ID card with photograph\n*   For infants/minors, a birth certificate or school ID is often accepted.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Foreign Nationals:** Foreign nationals *do* need a passport to travel on flights within India.\n*   **International Flights:** If your flight connects to an international destination, you will need a passport, even if part of the journey is within India.\n*   **Airline Specifics:** While the general rule is that a passport is not required for domestic travel for Indian citizens, it is always a good idea to check the specific requirements of the airline you are flying with, just in case.\n*   **Security:** Airport security personnel have the final say. While the above documents are generally accepted, they can ask for additional verification if they deem it necessary.\n\nIn short, for Indian citizens on domestic flights, a valid photo ID is sufficient, and a passport is not mandatory.\n",
